<p class="indent">
  We can investigate the structural stability of the second order model by adding a
  friction term. (Recall that this term represents also the share of intracellular
  resources between daughter cells when the limiting factor has non-heritable effects,
  see our discution on friction in the previous article.)
</p>
<table class="equation-star">
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td>
        <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block" class="equation">
          <mfrac>
            <mrow>
              <mstyle mathvariant="italic">
                <mi>d</mi>
                <mi>r</mi>
                <msub>
                  <mrow></mrow>
                  <mrow>
                    <mi>A</mi>
                  </mrow>
                </msub>
              </mstyle>
            </mrow>
            <mrow>
              <mstyle mathvariant="italic">
                <mi>d</mi>
                <mi>t</mi>
              </mstyle>
            </mrow>
          </mfrac>
          <mo class="MathClass-rel">=</mo>
          <mfrac>
            <mrow>
              <mi>a</mi>
              <mi>φ</mi>
            </mrow>
            <mrow>
              <mi>A</mi>
              <mo class="MathClass-bin">+</mo>
              <mi>G</mi>
