          </mrow>
        </math>
      </td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>
<p class="indent">
  It turns out that in the case where there is coexistence, two scenarii are
  possible:
</p>

<ol class="enumerate1">
  <li class="enumerate" id="x1-15002x1">
    The polynomial has three negative roots: in this case the system converges
    exponentially toward equilibrium
  </li>
  <li class="enumerate" id="x1-15004x2">
    or the polynomial has a negative root and two conjugated complex
    solutions. In this case the system is stable or unstable according to the
    sign of the real part of the roots. In the case where the system is stable,
    the regime is pseudoperiodical with damped oscillations.
  </li>
</ol>
<p class="indent">
  The literal resolution of the polynomial can be easily realized, but the literal
  expression of the solutions is too complicated to be informative.
</p>

